### What is a server? 
A server is a physical or virtualize computer hosting the entire web infrastructure
### What is the role of the domain name?
Domain name System (foobar.com)  maps the text based address to a numerical based address understood by the computer
### What type of DNS record www is in www.foobar.com?
CNAME Canonical  name
### What is the role of the web server?
Web server (Nginx) Listens for HTTP request and serve static content like HTML and images and route request to the application server for dynamic content

### What is the role of the application server? 
Application server executes server side code and serve dynamic content 

### What is the role of the database
Database stores and retrieves data from the web application using structured quary language(SQL)

### What is the server using to communicate with the computer of the user requesting the website ?
The server uses HTTP protocol to communicate with the user to handle request and serve web content

## Infrasstructure Problem

### Single Point of  Failure
The entire infrastructure relies on one server which will result it downtime in the event of failure

### Downtime during code deployment or maintenance
Risk of downtime as the server may need to be restarted during code deployment

### Limited Capacity
The system may break down if it encounter unsual high traffic with no mean of scaling rapidly

